<br>
First, I'm assuming a lot of this is due to the recent Sontalak burns, since the Kunark stuff was farmed for months and was constantly approved by Verant.  But they nerf it so that Sontalak, Klandicar, etc. are still burnable but the really trivial stuff isn't?<br>
<br>
Second, they nerfed EVERY mob under 33k hp?  WTF, why?  Half my burns were actually in exp groups when we got in a tight bind - an Elite add in Ssra, one of those brown lizards that can channel CH's like a mofo in CT, etc.  Now they're all immune?  They nerfed 99% of the &quot;legitimate strategic&quot; uses for Manaburn to keep people from burning 4 specific mobs?  Now this is just stupidity in its purest form, and is my major complaint with this change, it makes this skill totally worthless in exp groups, which is when it can shine the most (since the damage, especially now without crits, is only a tiny drop in the bucket against the Luclin mobs).<br>
<br>
Third, I guess this is a big HAHAHAHA to all you small guilds out there from Verant, looks like you can't kill epic mobs as easily, or in some cases at all, anymore.  On the other hand, they can't stop farming of Kunark mobs.  So, 5 wizards and a puller can't kill them anymore.  But 5 wizards, a warrior, and a cleric can kill them just as easily using normal spells.  Won't solve much, really.  As long as totally easy, trivial mobs drop CoF's, they WILL be farmed.  Adding the Damage 3 effect to the WDSC won't lessen the competition for these mobs at all, wizards are STILL the most damaging class against Kunark dragons and can still farm them with ease... unless they make all mobs under 33K immune to Sunstrike.<br>
<br>
Now, have fun burning Sontalak for the next month until melees upset that they can't easily farm sleepers keys complain to Verant and MB gets nerfed on all mobs under 150k hp... <p><a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/profile.php?pid=119">Master Aledar Boomcaster</a><br>Sorcerer of <a href="http://www.reconstructed.nu/">Reconstructed</a>, E'ci<br><img src="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bwa/bunnypet.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br>  Posts: 3069<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 9:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://chuma.cas.usf.edu/~dking3..._small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MANABURN - NERFED ON TEST!</span><hr size=1> Shit <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unicolheartsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 692<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 9:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.hiwaay.net/~kostrom/erudite.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MANABURN - NERFED ON TEST!</span><hr size=1> And the real problem with manaburn in PvP untouched,<br>
